
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" dir="ltr">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title> Twitter Sentiment Analysis</title>
  </head>
  <body>

    <div class="dropdown">
      <button class="dropdown-btn">Help?</button>
      <div class="dropdown-content">
        <p class="desc">
          Type in a Twitter users handle to see the sentiment graph of their last 200 tweets.
          For example, try typing "@realDonaldTrump" to see the POTUS's sentiment graph.
          Hover over the individual bar graph to see the individual tweet.
          On the graph, the most recent tweets are shown left to right.
          You can also click "Show tweets" to show a list of all the tweets analyzed.
          If there seems to be "gaps" in the graph, or a bit of space between each bar, it means the analysis deemed the post "nuetral,"
          and therefore received a score of 0%.
          Also, if the bar's are thicker than normal it means the user you typed in has less than 200 tweets.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h1>{{title}}</h1>
    <i>Explore twitter user's sentiment over time...</i>

    <h3>Popular users:
        <a class="popular">@realDonaldTrump</a>
        <a class="popular">@kanyewest</a>
        <a class="popular">@BillGates</a>
    </h3>

    <form class="style-form" action="" method="post">
      <div>
        <input name="user_id" placeholder="Ex: @jimmykimmel or @katyperry or @Snowden or one of your friends!" required/>
        <button class="go-btn" type="submit" name="button">GO!</button>
      </div>
    </form>

<main id="main" role="main" aria-live="assertive">

  <div class="chart description">
    <div id="chart-container"></div>
  </div>


    <div class ="description">
      <button class="tweets-btn" value="Hide tweets">Hide tweets</button>
      <div class="tweets">
        {{#each tweets}}
        <p>
          {{this.tweet.user.name}}
          <div>
            {{this.tweet.created_at}}
          </div>
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            {{this.text}}
          </li>
          <hr />
        </ul>
        {{/each}}
      </div>
    </div>
</main>



